# CorePHP — Cursor IDE Rules
# Applied to all completions and Composer interactions in this workspace.

## Project Identity
CorePHP is a PHP 8.4 base Docker image ("PHP-JVM") providing:
- Persistent process model via RoadRunner
- Type-safe `std` library under `core\` namespace
- Engine-level safety via runkit7 + php.ini hardening
- Zero silent failures — every error is a typed exception

## Commands
```bash
make build      # Build Docker image
make up         # Start services
make test       # PHPUnit (inside Docker)
make lint       # PHPStan Level 9 + PHP-CS-Fixer (inside Docker)
make lint-fix   # Auto-fix style violations
make shell      # Enter container
```

## Namespace Tree — All Core Classes
```
core\Any                                 — Universal strict base class
core\StrictObject                        — Undefined property guard (abstract)
core\Vec                                 — Typed sequential list
core\Dict                                — Typed key-value store
core\IO                                  — Safe file + HTTP facade
core\Engine\FunctionOverrider            — runkit7 override installer
core\Internal\Array\TypedCollection      — Base type-safe collection
core\Net\Http\HttpClient                 — curl wrapper (throws on failure)
core\Net\Http\HttpResponse               — Immutable response value object
core\Net\Http\HttpException              — HTTP + transport failures
core\Security\Exceptions\SecurityException
core\Security\Exceptions\EncodingException
```

## Exception Types
```
\RuntimeException
  └── core\Net\Http\HttpException
  └── core\Security\Exceptions\SecurityException
  └── core\Security\Exceptions\EncodingException

PSL (azjezz/psl ^4.2):
  Psl\Json\Exception                       — JSON decode/encode
  Psl\File\Exception\RuntimeException      — File read/write
  Psl\Type\Exception\CoercionException     — Type coercion
  Psl\Regex\Exception\RuntimeException     — Regex failures
```

## Global Shim Functions (available everywhere — no `use` needed)
```php
// JSON
s_json(string $json, bool $assoc = true): mixed
s_enc(mixed $val, bool $pretty = false): string

// Type coercion
s_int(mixed $val): int
s_float(mixed $val): float
s_str(mixed $val): string
s_bool(mixed $val): bool

// File I/O
s_file(string $path): string
s_write(string $path, string $data, bool $append = false): int
s_append(string $path, string $data): int
s_fwrite(resource $handle, string $data): int

// Regex
s_match(string $pattern, string $subject): bool
s_regex(string $pattern, string $subject): ?array
s_regex_all(string $pattern, string $subject): array

// Environment
s_env(string $key): string
s_env_or(string $key, string $default): string

// HTTP
s_get(string $url, array $headers = []): core\Net\Http\HttpResponse
s_post(string $url, array|string $body = [], array $headers = []): core\Net\Http\HttpResponse

// Array ↔ Collection bridge
arr_to_list(string $type, array $items): core\Vec
list_to_arr(core\Internal\Array\TypedCollection $list): array
arr_to_dict(string $type, array $data): core\Dict
dict_to_arr(core\Dict $dict): array

// Functional
vec_filter(iterable $list, callable $fn): array
vec_map(iterable $list, callable $fn): array
dict_filter(array $dict, callable $fn): array
dict_map(array $dict, callable $fn): array
dict_merge(array ...$dicts): array
```

## Hard Rules — Always Apply in Completions

### MUST
- Add `declare(strict_types=1);` as the first line of every PHP file
- Use `core\*` namespace for all new classes
- Declare explicit return types on all public methods
- Use `core\Vec` / `core\Dict` instead of `array` in public method signatures
- Throw typed, named exceptions — never return `false` / `null` / `0` as errors
- Write PHPUnit test before implementation code (TDD)

### MUST NOT
- Use `mixed` in any public method signature
- Use bare `array` type in public interfaces
- Silence exceptions with empty catch blocks
- Call `json_decode()` / `json_encode()` directly — use `s_json()` / `s_enc()`
- Call `file_get_contents()` / `file_put_contents()` — use `s_file()` / `s_write()`
- Call `intval()` / `floatval()` — use `s_int()` / `s_float()`
- Reference `core\Security\Safe\Safe` — **this class was deleted**
- Upgrade `azjezz/psl` past `^4.2` — phpstan extension is incompatible with PSL 5.x
- Use `unserialize()`, `exec()`, `shell_exec()`, `system()`, `eval()`

## File Layout
```
opt/corephp-vm/std/src/      — std library source (core\ namespace)
opt/corephp-vm/std/tests/    — PHPUnit tests (mirrors src/ structure)
opt/corephp-vm/bootstrap.php — auto_prepend_file sandbox
config/php.ini               — hardened PHP config
Makefile                     — all developer tasks
ci/lint.sh                   — PHPStan + PHP-CS-Fixer runner
ci/test.sh                   — PHPUnit runner
memory-bank/                 — GOS project documentation
docs/std/                    — std library API docs
```

## Gotchas
- `TypedCollection` is NOT `final` — `Vec` extends it
- `HttpResponse::header()` returns `?string` (null if absent); use `requireHeader()` to throw
- `FunctionOverrider::install()` is idempotent — safe to call multiple times
- `bootstrap.php` has a `PHP_JVM_BOOTSTRAP_LOADED` guard against double-loading
